<title type="html"><![CDATA[arcade ports with different resoultions]]></title>

<content type="html" xml:base="http://forums.nesdev.com/viewtopic.php?t=7752&amp;p=78154#p78154"><![CDATA[
Fighting game sprites themselves were often resized down from hand-drawn animation cels, using high-quality scaling algorithms, and then had outline effects (aka "<a href="http://pixel-zone.rpgdx.net/shtml/tut-selout1.shtml" class="postlink">selout</a>") applied.<p>Statistics: Posted by <a href="http://forums.nesdev.com/memberlist.php?mode=viewprofile&amp;u=9">tepples</a> — Sat May 14, 2011 5:26 pm</p><hr />
]]></content>
